The UTM is a complete framework that provides detailed assessments clients entire security infrastructures to identify, 
manage and eliminate any vulnerability and failure.

UTM is an advanced centralized solutions and configurations for distributed environments, 
well you can deploy sets of configurations instances.

Native LABS’s UTM is hosted on Native LABs data centers, where we keep on your network, and could help your administrators and 
engineers to monitor the infrastructure and solve many issues.

Native LABS provide two kinds of clients agent appliance over MIPS architecture and light programs that you can host on your data center.
The Native LABS’s UTM core is an automatos developed with C and Python, that’s based on a modular architecture.



Features:
Infrastructure design
Equipment Specifications
System Testing
Risk and Vulnerability Assessment
Security Systems Planning
Audit and full reporting
Patch and upgrade management
Notification system (Mail, SMSC, Radio, XMPP, ...)

Technologies :
Database : Postgresql, Cassandra, MySQL, DB2
Language : Html5, XML, Yaml, Python, C
Tools    : Lex, Yacc, Evenbright, RabittMQ, Redis, Flask, Scala
Modelisation : Prolog, Z
Communities : RIPE, Debian, IETF, GNU, Kernel


Partner : EMI, INPT, ENSIAS, Mohammed VI Science faculty ( Rabat ), J. Chrozerbeck, FAR


